More and more parents are using people-tracking devices to control their children
The fear of children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also track the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in the case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka Janatkov<0xC3><0xA1>.
At the moment the device is about the size of a matchbox, but will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people feared the case of the missing Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka and began to report on the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
“We’re all trying to tell ourselves that it’s not about spying, but about another means to lessen the chances of a tragedy happening,” says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that, in certain cases, you can abuse such devices, for example if they get into someone's bag without their knowledge, but we have not yet come across such cases."
“Most customers actually buy it for security reasons,” Pilin adds.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how to use it in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bo<0xC4><0x8D>kov<0xC3><0xA1> warns about the fact that, if the child does not want to carry it, he will simply throw it away.
“Even young children show great creativity in intentionally losing certain things if they want to avoid being controlled.”
“In the past, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” says Bo<0xC4><0x8D>kov<0xC3><0xA1>.
In his opinion, it is debatable if in case of attack such a device is really useful.
“If it’s a pre-arranged kidnapping, the author will almost always check if the child is wearing any kind of electronic device that can reveal their location.”
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices is extended, you will also look for them, since their sale will undoubtedly be carried out with a lot of advertising."
“In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised attack from a pedophile.
According to Robert <0xC4><0x8C>ech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can help.
"The device can be configured to regularly send the position after a certain period."
"If he suffers damage, at least it will facilitate the last position of the person in question."
“The most expensive devices have an incline meter integrated, so if the person simply slips and remains motionless, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” says <0xC4><0x8C>ech.
