Aid donors consider the election of a legitimate and popular government to be an essential step in Haiti’s reconstruction.
And, as it has become evident, so do the Haitians themselves.
Moving from pointers to center
In the weeks since losing her husband, Cristina Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez, the president of Argentina, has enjoyed a great sympathy among the public that has increased its popularity index by 20 points, to more than 50%, the highest level it has recorded since its election in 2007.
