It is unclear whether President Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez wants to remain in politics when her term ends, given that she no longer has her husband by her side.
If he does, he will need the support of the middle class, much of which has grown tired of Kirchnerism.
When the Argentines return from their summer vacation in March, the wave of sympathy for her will have waned.
If you want to win other elections, you will have to decide whether or not to repudiate, with peace of mind, many of your husband’s policies.
