The ECSC rejects a second wave of mergers in the boxes
The Director-General of the ECSC, José Antonio Olavarrieta, ruled out yesterday that there will be a wave of mergers of savings banks and once again insisted on the speed with which the restructuring of the sector is being carried out.
When he started the process of concentrating the Spanish savings banks, there were several entities that ensured that they would not participate in this first phase and that they would be reserved for the second round.
